<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is the best AI image generator overall?</h3>
<p>Midjourney remains a top overall AI image generator in 2026, with outstanding artistic quality, photorealism, and compositional depth. Its Version 7 model delivers cinematic results that outperform competitors for creative and design work.</p>

<h3>Which AI image generator handles text in images best?</h3>
<p>Ideogram is a top AI image generator for text rendering, achieving approximately 90% accuracy on text in images. It far outperforms Midjourney and DALL-E for creating posters, ads, logos, and social media graphics with legible embedded text.</p>

<h3>Is there a free AI image generator that's actually good?</h3>
<p>Yes, Stable Diffusion is a completely free, open-source AI image generator that is extremely powerful. It offers unparalleled customization through fine-tuning, LoRAs, and ControlNet. DALL-E 3 is also available at no extra cost to ChatGPT Plus subscribers.</p>

<h3>Which AI image generator is best for vector graphics and logos?</h3>
<p>Recraft is the only AI image generator that outputs actual SVG vector graphics, making it a top choice for logos, icons, and branding materials. It also offers brand kit features for maintaining style consistency across all generated assets.</p>

<h3>Which AI image generator is best for beginners?</h3>
<p>DALL-E 3 by OpenAI is a top choice for beginners. Its natural language understanding is exceptional — you simply describe what you want and it delivers with minimal prompt engineering. Tight integration with ChatGPT makes it accessible to anyone.</p>

<h3>Which AI image generator is best for YouTube thumbnails?</h3>
<p>Ideogram is a top choice for YouTube thumbnails because of its excellent text rendering — ideal for adding attention-grabbing text overlays. Midjourney is better if you want purely visual thumbnails without text.</p>

<h3>Can I use AI-generated images commercially?</h3>
<p>Yes, most platforms allow commercial use of generated images. Midjourney's paid plans include commercial licensing. DALL-E 3 grants full ownership of generated images. Stable Diffusion is open-source with flexible licensing. Always check each platform's specific terms for commercial use restrictions.</p>

<h3>Which AI is best for anime-style art?</h3>
<p>Stable Diffusion is a top choice for anime-style art due to its extensive ecosystem of fine-tuned models (like Anything V5 and counterfeit). Leonardo AI also offers specialized anime models. Midjourney produces anime styles but with less genre-specific accuracy.</p>

<h3>Is Midjourney better than DALL-E?</h3>
<p>Midjourney produces higher artistic quality and photorealism. DALL-E 3 is easier to use and has better natural language understanding. For professional creative work, Midjourney wins. For quick, reliable results without learning prompt engineering, DALL-E is better.</p>

<h3>Which AI image generator is cheapest?</h3>
<p>Stable Diffusion is completely free (open-source, run locally). DALL-E 3 is included with ChatGPT Plus ($20/month). Ideogram offers a generous free tier. Recraft and Leonardo both have free tiers with daily credits. Midjourney starts at $10/month.</p>

